Vice President Mike Pence, Chairman of the National Space Council, has announced the candidates selected to serve on the National Space Council's Users Advisory Group. Pending official appointment by the Administrator of NASA, these individuals will fulfill President Trump's mandate to foster coordination, cooperation, and technology and information exchange in the US space enterprise. The announcement was made on the eve of the second meeting of the National Space Council. The selected members include notable figures such as Buzz Aldrin, Tory Bruno, Wes Bush, Eileen Collins, Newt Gingrich, Marillyn Hewson, and Gwynne Shotwell, among others.